version.updateMessage: The concept set is being added at same time as Pulmonay Embolism is being removed from the CHRONIC LUNG DISEASE concept set.  The CHRONIC LUNG DISEASE concept set aligns with the Charlson Comorbidity.  The CDC identifies Pulmonary Embolism as Chronic Lung Disease even though not all acute cases result in a chronic condition. https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/need-extra-precautions/people-with-medical-conditions.html
